external_knowledge:
- "giants in the social media jungle" refers to the users whose posts are the most popular;
- "posts have attracted the most admirers" metaphorically refers to the posts with the highest number of likes;
- "top three" refers to the limit of the top three users based on the ranking of their posts.

- Influence is measured by the number of followers and posts;
- The term 'influential' here refers to users with a high number of followers and posts, indicating they are popular and active;
- The popularity of a user is indicated by the number of followers they have;
- The activity level of a user is determined by the number of posts they have made.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.username
FROM users u
INNER JOIN likes l ON u.user_id = l.user_id;

SELECT username, bio
FROM users
WHERE email = 'example@example.com';

SELECT AVG(likes_count) AS average_likes_per_post
FROM posts
WHERE user_id = 1;
